{
  "texts": [
    "More than 65% of the participants responded with frequent consumption of fried or processed foods, while 15.31% responded with strong nutritional awareness while ordering.",
    "This implies that the food usually ordered contains too much oil, salt, and sugar but insufficient essential nutrients such as fiber, minerals, and vitamins.",
    "While nutritional information is relevant to consumers, it is missing, difficult to interpret, or inconsistent on food ordering platforms.",
    "This limits consumers from making enlightened choices, although consumers know.",
    "Although consumers intend to choose healthier versions of food, platform design and default menu options rarely facilitate such a habit."
  ]
}